        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 1:47PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 147 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Elbert, or 36 miles southeast of Denver, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree branches and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kiowa and rural locations in southwest Elbert County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
